This program reads USGS 30-sec terrain dataset in 33 tiles and converts it one single NetCDF file.
Only changes to raw data is for the Caspain sea.

1. Unpack USGS source data in gtopo30 directory:

   cd gtopo30
   source unpack.sh

FYI: The GTOPO30 data has been downloaded from USGS and placed in the gtopo30/data directory

    ftp ftp://edcftp.cr.usgs.gov
    cd /data/gtopo30/global
    mget *

2. Compile create_netCDF_from_USGS using make

   Note: big-endian compiler flag

3. Output file: usgs-rawdata.nc (size is approximately 7.5GB)


